The paper also discusses the complexity of these problems in sparse and unweighted graphs, which are common assumptions in the study of algorithms and data structures. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
